Regarding the explanation of `flatMap` argument:
* Each integer from the `s1` stream is mapped into `Stream&lt;tuple&gt;` containing several items: for each integer a string is picked from `Stream&lt;String&gt;`

* Thus, these multiple `Stream&lt;tuple&gt;` should be _flattened_ into a single `Stream&lt;tuple&gt;` which is consumed then in `forEach` terminal operation
```java
List&lt;Integer&gt; s1 = Stream.of(1, 2);
Supplier&lt;Stream&lt;String&gt;&gt; s2 = () -&gt; Stream.of(&quot;A&quot;, &quot;B&quot;);

s1  // Stream&lt;Integer&gt;
.flatMap(v1 -&gt; s2.get() // Stream&lt;String&gt; returned by the Supplier
                 .map(v2 -&gt; tuple(v1,v2)) // Stream&lt;tuple&gt;
) // Stream&lt;tuple&gt;
.forEach(System.out::println);
```
